Mix cornstarch and 3/4 cup broth. Mix remaining broth, oregano, garlic, broccoli, carrots and onion in saucepot. Heat to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add cornstarch mixture. Cook and stir until mixture boils and thickens. Stir in tomato. Toss with spaghetti and serve with cheese.